# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# CardTone — Environment Variables for Contributors
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# HOW TO USE:
#   1. Create your own Supabase project at https://supabase.com (free tier works)
#   2. Run the SQL schema from SUPABASE_SETUP.md in the Supabase SQL Editor
#   3. Copy this file:   cp .env.example .env
#   4. Fill in YOUR project's URL and anon key below
#
# WHERE TO FIND THESE VALUES:
#   Supabase Dashboard → Settings → API
#   • Project URL  → SUPABASE_URL
#   • anon / public key → SUPABASE_ANON_KEY
#
# SECURITY NOTE:
#   The anon key is a PUBLIC key — it is safe to share locally, but your
#   Supabase database must have proper Row-Level Security (RLS) policies.
#   See THREAT_ANALYSIS.md for the recommended production RLS setup.
#   Never commit your .env file to git.
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-id.supabase.co
SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...
